{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TaG8ZvUyKz6qTkNbJDRRry","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me review the acceptance criteria for US-002:\n\n1. **Installer checks for `ddev` and `warden` binaries on the system PATH** - This is already implemented in `DdevDetector.Detect()` and `WardenDetector.Detect()` using `exec.LookPath`.\n\n2. **Detected environments show their name and version** - This is already implemented. In the selection phase view (`phaseSelection`), the code shows `env.Env.Name` and `env.Env.Version`.\n\n3. **If only one environment is detected, it is selected automatically without prompting** - This is already implemented in `advanceFromDetection()`. \n\n4. **If both are detected, a selection screen lets the user choose** - When multiple environments are found, the flow moves to `phaseSelection` where users can pick one.\n\n5. **If neither is detected, a clear error message is shown with links to install DDEV or Warden** - When no environments are found, the flow goes to `phaseError`, which displays the error message and installation URLs from each detector.\n\n6. **Detection runs asynchronously with a spinner while in progress** - The spinner is initialized and ticked globally throughout the entire flow, handling `spinner.TickMsg` events in the update loop. The `phaseDetecting` state displays the spinner while the environment detection command runs.\n\nWait, I need to trace through this more carefully. When the user presses Enter on the directory before detection completes, the phase switches to `phaseDetecting`, which shows a spinner with \"Detecting development...\" text. Since `detectEnvironments` is fired as an async command in `Init()` and the spinner ticks are handled globally, the detection runs in the background while the spinner animates. So this criterion is satisfied - detection is truly asynchronous and the UI shows a spinner during that time.\n\nLet me run the tests to verify everything works as expected.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15408,"cache_read_input_tokens":31889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":15408},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e204eeb6-4b6e-491a-8813-b964c2999bbd","uuid":"2ad4dae4-1142-498b-9c25-07629a472f65"}
