{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FaH3sDvZdVz7WA27XAfn8E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All tests pass. Now I need to review each acceptance criterion one by one to see if any are missing or need improvement:\n\n1. **Installer checks for `ddev` and `warden` binaries on the system PATH.** ✅ - Implemented in `DdevDetector.Detect()` and `WardenDetector.Detect()`\n\n2. **Detected environments show their name and version.** ✅ - In `phaseSelection`, shows `env.Env.Name` and `env.Env.Version`\n\n3. **If only one environment is detected, it is selected automatically without prompting.** ✅ - `advanceFromDetection()` handles single env case\n\n\n4. **If both are detected, a selection screen lets the user choose.** ✅ - Goes to `phaseSelection`\n\n5. **If neither is detected, a clear error message is shown with links to install DDEV or Warden.** ✅ - Goes to `phaseError` with links\n\n6. **Detection runs asynchronously with a spinner while in progress.** - Let me check this more carefully. The `Init()` method batches the spinner tick with the detection command, so the spinner should animate while detection happens in the background.\n\nLooking at the view logic, the spinner only appears during `phaseDetecting`, but the detection itself starts immediately in `Init()`. The issue is that the user might complete the name and directory input phases before detection finishes, so the spinner only shows if they press Enter before the detection completes. This seems acceptable since detection is genuinely running asynchronously the whole time. Looking at the test failures for US-002, I need to check whether the required tests actually exist. The criteria demand that the installer verifies both `ddev` and `warden` binaries are on the system PATH, and I can see both detectors are implemented with `exec.LookPath` calls, so that's covered. For the second criterion about showing environment names and versions