{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015d5DTupa2VfaBvAp5qvXeP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me verify all acceptance criteria are met:\n\n**AC1: Warden environment is initialized with `warden env-init`.**\n✅ Step 0 in `Install()` calls `warden env-init <projectName> magento2`.\n\n**AC2: SSL certificates are signed for both `<project>.test` and `app.<project>.test`.**\n✅ Step 1 calls `warden sign-certificate <project>.test` AND `warden sign-certificate app.<project>.test`.\n\n**AC3: Warden services are started.**\n✅ Step 2 calls `warden env up`.\n\n**AC4: Installer waits for PHP-FPM to be ready before running composer.**\n✅ Step 4 runs `while ! command -v composer &>/dev/null; do sleep 1; done` in the php-fpm container before composer create-project.\n\n**AC5: `auth.json` is copied into the container's composer home with correct ownership.**\n✅ Step 6 calls `wardenCopyAuthJSONComposerHome()` which copies the file and runs `chown www-data:www-data`.\n\n**AC6: `setup:install` runs in the `php-fpm` container with correct flags.**\n✅ Step 7 runs `warden env exec php-fpm bin/magento setup:install` with all flags from `SetupInstallFlags()` including `--base-url`.\n\n**AC7: Application settings (base URL, caching, search) are configured via `bin/magento config:set` after install.**\n✅ Step 8 runs multiple `config:set` commands for base URLs, cache, SSL, SEO rewrites, etc.\n\n**AC8: The store is accessible at `https://app.<project>.test/` with HTTP 200.**\n✅ `verifyInstallation()` is called at the end checking HTTP 200 on `https://app.<project>.test/`.\n\n**AC9: Response includes `x-dist: Mage-OS` header.**\n✅ `verifyInstallation()` checks that the `x-dist` header contains `\"Mage-OS\"`.\n\n<chief-done/>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":599,"cache_read_input_tokens":50342,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_t