{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0125Um2gqvizJpDbSJTdTZAa","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t## Codebase Patterns\n2\t- Uses Bubble Tea TUI framework (`github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea`) with a central `Model` and phase-based state machine\n3\t- Text inputs use `github.com/charmbracelet/bubbles/textinput`\n4\t- Phases are defined as `phase int` constants (e.g., `phaseNameInput`, `phaseDirectoryInput`, etc.)\n5\t- Detection runs in background goroutine, results cached in model until user advances\n6\t- Tests are in `internal/tui/tui_test.go` using `sendMsg()` helper to drive state transitions\n7\t- Run tests with `/usr/local/go/bin/go test ./...`\n8\t- Detector tests live in `internal/detector/detector_test.go` and use `allDetectors()` (package-internal) to inspect all registered detectors\n9\t- TUI view tests call `m.View()` directly and use a local `contains()` helper to assert rendered output\n10\t- `DdevDetector.buildSteps()` and `WardenDetector.buildSteps()` both append \"Verify installation\" as the last step always; use `len(d.steps) - 1` for its index in `Install()` (optional steps are dynamic)\n11\t- `verifyInstallation()` in `ddev.go` is unexported but shared; test it from `package detector` tests using `httptest.NewServer`\n12\t- Warden's `BaseURL` returns `\"https://app.<name>.test\"` (no trailing slash); append `\"/\"` when used in config:set and setup:install `--base-url`\n13\t\n14\t---\n15\t\n16\t## [2026-04-14] - US-004\n17\t- All implementation for sample data was already in place:\n18\t  - `installSampleData bool` field in `Model` (default `false`, set in `initSetupInputs()`)\n19\t  - Toggle rendered in `phaseSetupConfig` view with `[ ]`/`[x]` checkbox\n20\t  - Space bar handler in `Update()` at `toggleFocus == -2` toggles the flag\n21\t  - `Config.InstallSampleData` field in `config.go`\n22\t  - `buildSteps()` in both `ddev.go` and `warden.go` conditionally appends \"Install sample data\" step\n23\t  - `Install()` in both detectors conditionally runs `sampledata:deploy` + `setup:upgrade` + `cache:flush`\n24\t  - CI matrix in `.github/workflows/build-and-test.yml` has `regular`/`sampledata` variants for both DDEV and Warden\n25\t- Added 6 new unit tests:\n26\t  - `TestSampleData_DefaultIsOff` — installSampleData is false after initSetupInputs\n27\t  - `TestSampleData_ToggledBySpace` — space on the toggle enables/disables it\n28\t  - `TestSampleData_ViewContainsToggle` — view contains \"Install sample data\" label\n29\t  - `TestSampleData_ViewShowsChecked` — view shows `[x]` when enabled\n30\t  - `TestDdevBuildSteps_SampleDataStep` — step present/absent based on config\n31\t  - `TestWardenBuildSteps_SampleDataStep` — step present/absent based on config\n32\t- Files changed:\n33\t  - `internal/tui/tui_test.go`\n34\t  - `internal/detector/detector_test.go`\n35\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n36\t  - For stories marked \"passes: false\" where implementation already exists, the missing piece is usually explicit unit tests covering each acceptance criterion\n37\t  - To navigate to the sample data toggle in tests: Tab `len(setupFieldDefs)` times from the first admin field\n38\t  - `toggleFocus == -2` is the sample data toggle; `toggleFocus == -1` is the Hyvä toggle — this is the navigation model\n39\t---\n40\t\n41\t## [2026-04-14] - US-011\n42\t- Added \"Verify installation\" as the last step in `WardenDetector.buildSteps()` (was missing, matching DDEV pattern)\n43\t- Added `--base-url` flag to `WardenDetector.SetupInstallFlags()` using `d.BaseURL(config.ProjectName) + \"/\"` (was missing)\n44\t- Added verify step execution at the end of `WardenDetector.Install()` using `verifyInstallation()` (shared with DDEV)\n45\t- Added 7 new tests covering: base steps, verify-is-last, base URL format, `--base-url` flag, DB flags, Redis cache flags, OpenSearch flags\n46\t- Files changed:\n47\t  - `internal/detector/warden.go`\n48\t  - `internal/detector/detector_test.go`\n49\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n50\t  - Warden's `Install()` uses a slice of closures (`allSteps []func() error`) iterated by index — different from DDEV's sequential steps slice. The verify step is appended AFTER the loop.\n51\t  - `verifyInstallation()` is defined in `ddev.go` but used by both detectors (same package); no duplication needed.\n52\t  - Warden `BaseURL` returns no trailing slash; use `+ \"/\"` for Magento base URL configuration.\n53\t  - The step count for verify index must be computed from `len(d.steps) - 1` AFTER `buildSteps` is called at the top of `Install()`.\n54\t---\n55\t\n56\t## [2026-04-14] - US-001\n57\t- Verified that project name and install directory input phases were already fully implemented in `internal/tui/tui.go`\n58\t- `New()` seeds `nameInput` with `filepath.Base(cwd)` via `currentDirName()`\n59\t- `enterDirectoryPhase()` computes default directory via `defaultDirectory()`: cwd if name unchanged, `cwd/<name>` otherwise\n60\t- Both `nameInput` and `dirInput` are `textinput.Model` (editable text fields)\n61\t- Enter key advances through both phases\n62\t- All tests in `internal/tui/tui_test.go` pass\n63\t- Files involved: `internal/tui/tui.go` (no changes needed)\n64\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n65\t  - The codebase already had the full phase-based flow implemented; US-001 was a green-field verification\n66\t  - Test helpers: `sendMsg()`, `pressEnter()`, `makeDetectedEnv()` in `tui_test.go`\n67\t  - `originalName` field tracks the default so `defaultDirectory()` can distinguish user-changed vs default name\n68\t  - Detection runs in parallel via `detectEnvironments` cmd in `Init()`, results cached during input phases\n69\t---\n70\t\n71\t## [2026-04-14] - US-002\n72\t- Verified that all acceptance criteria were already implemented in the codebase:\n73\t  - `DdevDetector.Detect()` and `WardenDetector.Detect()` use `exec.LookPath` to check PATH\n74\t  - Both detectors registered in `allDetectors()` in `internal/detector/detector.go`\n75\t  - Selection phase view shows `env.Env.Name` and `env.Env.Version`\n76\t  - `advanceFromDetection()` auto-selects when 1 env, shows selection when >1, errors when 0\n77\t  - `phaseError` view shows install links via `detector.AllDetectorInfos()`\n78\t  - `detectEnvironments` Cmd launched in `Init()` runs asynchronously; `phaseDetecting` shows spinner\n79\t- Added targeted tests to explicitly cover all 6 acceptance criteria:\n80\t  - `TestDetectors_DdevAndWardenBothRegistered` — verifies both are in the registry\n81\t  - `TestDetectors_EnvironmentHasName` — verifies Detect() returns Environment with Name\n82\t  - `TestView_SelectionShowsNameAndVersion` — verifies version appears in selection view\n83\t  - `TestView_ErrorShowsInstallLinks` — verifies install links in error phase view\n84\t  - `TestView_DetectingPhaseShowsSpinner` — verifies \"Detecting\" text in detecting phase\n85\t- Files changed:\n86\t  - `internal/detector/detector_test.go` — new tests for detector registry and environment output\n87\t  - `internal/tui/tui_test.go` — new view tests + local `contains()` helper\n88\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n89\t  - `allDetectors()` is package-internal; use it in `detector` package tests but not from outside\n90\t  - TUI view tests are straightforward: set `m.phase` directly, call `m.View()`, assert on string content\n91\t  - Stories marked \"passes: false\" may already be fully implemented; always run tests first before writing new code\n92\t  - `TestDetectors_EnvironmentHasName` gracefully skips if binary not on PATH — good pattern for binary-dependent tests\n93\t---\n94\t\n95\t## [2026-04-14] - US-010\n96\t- Added `verifyInstallation()` to `internal/detector/ddev.go`: makes HTTP GET to base URL, checks HTTP 200 and `x-dist: Mage-OS` header; uses `InsecureSkipVerify` for DDEV's self-signed TLS certs\n97\t- Updated `DdevDetector.buildSteps()` to always append `{Name: \"Verify installation\"}` as the last step\n98\t- Updated `DdevDetector.Install()` to execute the verify step using `len(d.steps) - 1` as its index (avoids fragile nextIdx tracking across optional steps)\n99\t- Added 14 new tests in `internal/detector/detector_test.go`:\n100\t  - `TestDdevBuildSteps_BaseStepsPresent` — all required step names present\n101\t  - `TestDdevBuildSteps_VerifyIsLastStep` — verify is last across all optional combinations\n102\t  - `TestDdevSetupInstallFlags_DatabaseConfig` — db-host, db-name, db-user, db-password\n103\t  - `TestDdevSetupInstallFlags_RedisCacheConfig` — cache-backend=redis, page-cache=redis\n104\t  - `TestDdevSetupInstallFlags_RedisSessionConfig` — session-save=redis\n105\t  - `TestDdevSetupInstallFlags_OpenSearchConfig` — search-engine=opensearch\n106\t  - `TestDdevSetupInstallFlags_RabbitMQConfig` — amqp-host=rabbitmq\n107\t  - `TestDdevSetupInstallFlags_AdminCredentials` — all five admin fields\n108\t  - `TestDdevBaseURL_UsesProjectName` — https://<name>.ddev.site\n109\t  - `TestVerifyInstallation_Success` — httptest returning 200 + x-dist: Mage-OS\n110\t  - `TestVerifyInstallation_Non200` — error on 503\n111\t  - `TestVerifyInstallation_MissingXDistHeader` — error when header absent\n112\t  - `TestVerifyInstallation_WrongXDistHeader` — error when header is wrong value\n113\t- Files changed:\n114\t  - `internal/detector/ddev.go`\n115\t  - `internal/detector/detector_test.go`\n116\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n117\t  - The Hyvä block in `Install()` does NOT increment `nextIdx` after hyvaEnableIdx — always use `len(d.steps) - 1` to locate the verify step, not `nextIdx`\n118\t  - `httptest.NewServer` is the right pattern for testing HTTP client code in Go; plain `http.Handler` is enough, no TLS needed for unit tests (HTTPS skipping applies to real DDEV only)\n119\t  - `assertFlags()` helper added to `detector_test.go` — reuse it for future flag tests\n120\t---\n121\t\n122\t## [2026-04-14] - US-005\n123\t- All implementation for Hyvä theme was already in place:\n124\t  - `installHyva bool` field in `Model` (default `false`, set in `initSetupInputs()`)\n125\t  - Toggle rendered in `phaseSetupConfig` view with `[ ]`/`[x]` checkbox at `toggleFocus == -1`\n126\t  - Space bar handler in `Update()` at `toggleFocus == -1` toggles the flag\n127\t  - Hyvä credential fields (`hyvaFieldDefs`: Repo URL, Auth token) shown only when `m.installHyva == true`\n128\t  - `Config.InstallHyva`, `Config.HyvaRepoURL`, `Config.HyvaAuthToken` fields in `config.go`\n129\t  - `buildSteps()` in both `ddev.go` and `warden.go` conditionally appends \"Configure Hyvä repository\", \"Install Hyvä theme\", \"Enable Hyvä modules\" steps\n130\t  - `Install()` in both detectors conditionally runs composer config + require + module:enable + theme activation\n131\t  - CI matrix in `.github/workflows/build-and-test.yml` has `hyva` and `hyva-sampledata` variants for both DDEV and Warden\n132\t  - CI \"Check if this variant should run\" step skips Hyvä variants when `HYVA_REPO_URL` secret is not configured\n133\t- Added 8 new unit tests:\n134\t  - `TestHyva_DefaultIsOff` — installHyva is false after initSetupInputs\n135\t  - `TestHyva_ToggledBySpace` — space on the Hyvä toggle enables/disables it\n136\t  - `TestHyva_ViewContainsToggle` — view contains \"Install Hyvä\" label\n137\t  - `TestHyva_ViewShowsChecked` — view shows `[x]` when enabled\n138\t  - `TestHyva_CredentialFieldsHiddenByDefault` — Repo URL/Auth token not shown when disabled\n139\t  - `TestHyva_CredentialFieldsAppearsWhenEnabled` — Repo URL/Auth token shown when enabled\n140\t  - `TestDdevBuildSteps_HyvaSteps` — steps present/absent based on config for DDEV\n141\t  - `TestWardenBuildSteps_HyvaSteps` — steps present/absent based on config for Warden\n142\t- Files changed:\n143\t  - `internal/tui/tui_test.go`\n144\t  - `internal/detector/detector_test.go`\n145\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n146\t  - Navigate to Hyvä toggle in tests: Tab `len(setupFieldDefs) + 1` times from admin field 0\n147\t  - `navigateToHyvaToggle()` helper added to `tui_test.go` — reuse for future Hyvä-related tests\n148\t  - For stories marked \"passes: false\" where all implementation already exists, the missing piece is unit tests for each acceptance criterion\n149\t---\n150\t\n151\t## [2026-04-14] - US-003\n152\t- Added sensible defaults for admin email (`admin@example.com`) and password (`Admin123!`) in `setupFieldDefaults` — were previously empty strings\n153\t- Added 5 new tests in `internal/tui/tui_test.go` covering all acceptance criteria:\n154\t  - `TestSetupConfig_HasAllFiveFields` — all five field labels present in the view\n155\t  - `TestSetupConfig_DefaultsPreFilled` — all fields have non-empty defaults after initSetupInputs\n156\t  - `TestSetupConfig_TabAdvancesField` — Tab moves focus to next field\n157\t  - `TestSetupConfig_ShiftTabGoesBack` — Shift+Tab moves focus to previous field\n158\t  - `TestSetupConfig_ValidationRejectsEmpty` — empty required field blocks advance to preview\n159\t- Files changed:\n160\t  - `internal/tui/tui.go` — updated `setupFieldDefaults`\n161\t  - `internal/tui/tui_test.go` — new tests + `advanceToSetupConfig` helper\n162\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n163\t  - `setupFieldDefaults` drives default values; index order matches `setupFieldDefs` (user, password, email, firstname, lastname)\n164\t  - `advanceToSetupConfig()` is a reusable test helper: name→dir→setup config using a mock env\n165\t  - `inTogglePhase` and `toggleFocus` track whether focus is in the admin fields section or the toggle/Hyvä section — check both when asserting focus position\n166\t---\n167\t\n168\t## [2026-04-14] - US-012\n169\t- `.goreleaser.yml` already existed and was committed, but was invalid for GoReleaser v2\n170\t- Fixed two GoReleaser v2 incompatibilities:\n171\t  1. Added `version: 2` at the top (required; without it, GoReleaser v2 treats config as version 0 and rejects it)\n172\t  2. Changed `archives[].format: binary` → `archives[].formats: [binary]` (the `format` field is deprecated in v2)\n173\t- CI workflow `.github/workflows/build-and-test.yml` was already correctly configured:\n174\t  - `release` job has `needs: [go-test, ddev-test, warden-test]` (all tests must pass first)\n175\t  - `release` job has `if: startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/v')` (only on v* tags)\n176\t  - Uses `goreleaser/goreleaser/v2@latest` for releases\n177\t- Files changed:\n178\t  - `.goreleaser.yml` — added `version: 2`, changed `format: binary` → `formats: [binary]`\n179\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n180\t  - GoReleaser v2 requires `version: 2` at the top of the config; without it, the CLI rejects the file even if everything else is valid\n181\t  - `archives[].format` is deprecated in GoReleaser v2; use `archives[].formats` (array) instead\n182\t  - Run `go run github.com/goreleaser/goreleaser/v2@latest check` to validate the config without a real release\n183\t  - The workflow installs `goreleaser/v2@latest` — always validate config against v2 syntax\n184\t---\n185\t\n186\t## [2026-04-14] - US-013\n187\t- All acceptance criteria were already implemented in `.github/workflows/build-and-test.yml` except one:\n188\t  - `go-test` job runs `go test -v ./...` on every push ✅\n189\t  - `ddev-test` job has a 4-variant matrix (regular, sampledata, hyva, hyva-sampledata) ✅\n190\t  - `warden-test` job has the same 4-variant matrix ✅\n191\t  - Both jobs verify: binary runs (`bin/magento`), HTTP 200, `x-dist: Mage-OS` header ✅\n192\t  - Both jobs verify product count > 0 for sample data variants ✅\n193\t  - Both jobs verify `Hyva/default` theme in DB for Hyvä variants ✅\n194\t  - `warden-test` had a \"Debug on failure\" step; `ddev-test` was missing it ❌ → added\n195\t- Added \"Debug on failure\" step to `ddev-test` job (docker ps, .ddev/.env, container logs) matching the pattern in `warden-test`\n196\t- Files changed:\n197\t  - `.github/workflows/build-and-test.yml`\n198\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n199\t  - When a story has `\"passes\": false`, always compare each acceptance criterion line-by-line against the implementation — one missing step can be the only gap\n200\t  - Debug-on-failure steps use `if: failure() && steps.should-run.outputs.skip != 'true'` so they only run when the job actually failed and wasn't skipped\n201\t  - DDEV install directory in CI is `test-mageos/`; DDEV env files live at `test-mageos/.ddev/.env` and `test-mageos/.env`\n202\t---\n203\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27dbe6f2-4344-4ebd-9988-c8a54cc5d7bc","uuid":"c4f84339-af06-4752-870d-8ca4b8b6bb6e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T19:31:09.270Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/michielgerritsen/Sites/mage-os-install/.chief/prds/main/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- Uses Bubble Tea TUI framework (`github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea`) with a central `Model` and phase-based state machine\n- Text inputs use `github.com/charmbracelet/bubbles/textinput`\n- Phases are defined as `phase int` constants (e.g., `phaseNameInput`, `phaseDirectoryInput`, etc.)\n- Detection runs in background goroutine, results cached in model until user advances\n- Tests are in `internal/tui/tui_test.go` using `sendMsg()` helper to drive state transitions\n- Run tests with `/usr/local/go/bin/go test ./...`\n- Detector tests live in `internal/detector/detector_test.go` and use `allDetectors()` (package-internal) to inspect all registered detectors\n- TUI view tests call `m.View()` directly and use a local `contains()` helper to assert rendered output\n- `DdevDetector.buildSteps()` and `WardenDetector.buildSteps()` both append \"Verify installation\" as the last step always; use `len(d.steps) - 1` for its index in `Install()` (optional steps are dynamic)\n- `verifyInstallation()` in `ddev.go` is unexported but shared; test it from `package detector` tests using `httptest.NewServer`\n- Warden's `BaseURL` returns `\"https://app.<name>.test\"` (no trailing slash); append `\"/\"` when used in config:se