{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CtSbxXTZsvTyJEbtysT85A","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test `TestPreview_EnterAdvancesToInstall` fails because `tea.ExecProcess` needs to actually run the process or be stubbed. Looking at the code:\n\n```go\ncase \"enter\":\n    m.initInstallSteps()\n    // Cache sudo credentials before starting the install so that\n    // commands like \"ddev start\" (which modifies /etc/hosts) can\n    // use sudo without prompting inside the TUI.\n    c := exec.Command(\"sudo\", \"-v\")\n    return m, tea.ExecProcess(c, func(err error) tea.Msg {\n\n\n```\n\nHandling the sudo callback...\n\nWhen `sudoCachedMsg` arrives, the phase transitions to `phaseInstalling` and the install process kicks off with the spinner and command execution. The test only sends one Enter keypress, so without actually triggering the sudo message, the model remains stuck in `phaseSetupPreview`. I should verify that pressing Enter at least initializes the install steps by checking if `m.installSteps` gets populated, rather than relying on the phase change alone. check that `installSteps` was populated (not nil) after pressing Enter.\n\nLet me update the test to check that `initInstallSteps()` was called (i.e., `installSteps` is not nil), or we can send `sudoCachedMsg` afterward to check it transitions to `phaseInstalling`.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is to check that `m.installSteps` is populated after Enter (meaning `initInstallSteps()` was called). Or we can check the model doesn't stay in setup config... hmm.\n\nWait, looking at the code again: `initInstallSteps()` works by calling `m.selected.Detector.Steps()` which in our `mockDetector` returns `nil`. So `installSteps` would be `nil` after `initInstallSteps()`.\n\nLet me try a different approach: send the Enter key, then follow up with `sudoCachedMsg` to verify it transitions to `phaseInstalling`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":260,"cache_read_input_tokens":49242,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":260},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27dbe6f2-4344-4ebd-9988-c8a54cc5d7bc","uuid":"e989da03-7ee5-4349-8149-0c94b082e628"}
