ed to verify that installation steps have names visible after entering the install phase, that each step displays a status indicator, and a few other behaviors around step progression and completion.\n\nFor most of these tests, I can directly set `m.installSteps` with different statuses rather than mocking the detector, except when I specifically want to test that `initInstallSteps()` properly loads steps from the detector itself. Let me start writing out these test cases.\n\nI need to update the mock detector to include a `steps` field so it can return actual steps when `Steps()` is called, which won't affect existing tests since the default is nil. Then I'll write the test functions that verify each acceptance criterion.\n\nWriting test functions... Writing test helper functions... Writing test assertions... Writing test cases... Writing test cases... Writing test cases... Finishing the assertion for the step start message test, then moving on to verify that the done message properly transitions a step's status. Now I need to update the mock detector to support steps.\n\nAdding the Steps method to return the detector's steps...\n\nNow I should check the actual detector.Step type to ensure I'm implementing this correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4404,"cache_read_input_tokens":45819,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4404},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"258e2b76-815d-4c27-8bd0-a6a296178c24","uuid":"1d6d5dd9-cf0f-4bed-91ae-cb4d393d3a7a"}
