{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EaZWKja2ryK6z7HCiTV3Zt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No existing tests for the US-008 acceptance criteria. I need to write tests for:\n\n1. On failure, the error screen shows the last 10 log lines.\n2. Pressing `r` retries installation starting from the failed step.\n3. Already-completed steps are skipped on retry.\n4. Pressing Enter or `q` exits the installer.\n\nLet me review the current implementation to understand what needs testing:\n\nFrom `tui.go`:\n- `phaseInstallDone` view (line 878-909): Shows error with last 10 log lines\n- Key handler for `phaseInstallDone || phaseError` (lines 644-675):\n  - `r` key: retry from failed step (only when in `phaseInstallDone` with error)\n  - `enter`, `q`, `esc`: quit\n\nLooking at the implementation more carefully, the view code around line 884-896 displays up to 10 log lines when there's an installation error, and the key handler at lines 647-670 manages the `r` key for retrying when in the error phase. I need to create tests that verify each of these behaviors works as expected.\n\nFor the retry logic specifically, when `r` is pressed it finds the failed step index, sets `StartFromStep` to that index, marks incomplete steps as pending, and restarts the installation process. The handler at lines 671-673 also handles exit keys like enter, `q`, and `esc`. I should write tests covering all these scenarios.\n\nFor the `r` key test, I need to handle the fact that `runInstall` spawns a goroutine and returns a channel, but `sendMsg` discards that return value. I'll need to work around this when verifying the installation actually restarts. The goroutine starts immediately and sends an `installDoneMsg` to the buffered channel, but since `sendMsg` discards the command, `waitForLog` never gets called—the goroutine will complete and the channel will eventually close without anything reading from it.\n\nFor unit tests this is probably fine, though it could accumulate background goroutines if tests run many iterations. The real concern is that `runInstall` calls `os.MkdirAll(cfg.Directory, 0755)`, and I need to verify what directory gets set during the test setup—it looks like it defaults to the current working directory via `os.Getwd()`, which already exists, so `MkdirAll` should be safe.\n\nWriting test code... Writing test cases... Writing test cases... I'm writing a test that verifies pressing Enter on the error screen exits the installer by returning a tea.Quit command, though since sendMsg discards the command, I'm checking indirectly that the phase remains unchanged and the update doesn't panic.\n\nNow I'm adding a similar test for the 'q' key to ensure it also quits the installer, but I'm noticing there might be an issue with how the 'q' key is being handled in the Update function.\n\nLooking at the code structure, the 'q' key appears to be handled at the top level of Update, which means it should always trigger a quit regardless of the current phase. That's good for AC4 since we want 'q' to exit the installer on the error screen. But for the 'enter' key test, I need to verify it's being handled correctly in the phase-specific logic when we're in the install done or error phase.\n\nLet me trace through the code to see exactly where 'enter' is being processed... I need to call `Update` directly in the tests instead of using `sendMsg` so I can verify the returned command, since `sendMsg` discards it. This way I can properly assert that `q` triggers `tea.Quit` at the top level and `enter` triggers it in the `phaseInstallDone` handler. I'm realizing that since `tea.Quit` is a function in bubbletea, I can't directly compare it in tests, so the practical approach is to verify the command isn't nil and check that the model state behaves as expected rather than trying to assert the exact command returned. Now I'm looking at how the view renders the log display—it shows a \"Last output:\" header followed by the last 10 lines from the log, truncating anything older. I need to verify that the header appears, that exactly the last 10 lines are displayed (or fewer if there aren't that many), and that earlier lines are excluded, being careful to use distinct test strings to avoid substring matches. I need to use zero-padded formatting like `log-line-04` instead of `log-line-4` to avoid substring collisions when checking test output. For the retry test, I'm concerned about the goroutine that gets spawned during `Update` — it'll try to create the directory and call the detector's `Install` method, so I need to make sure the directory path is set up properly for the test.\n\nNow I'm thinking through what happens when the user presses `r` to trigger an install: the handler starts a goroutine that creates the directory, calls the mock detector's `Install`, and sends a completion message back through a channel that gets stored in the model. The test needs to account for this async behavior and the channel that persists after `sendMsg` returns.\n\nLooking at the `StartFromStep` logic, I need to understand how the handler finds the first failed step and then resets all non-completed steps back to pending status before restarting the installation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":372,"cache_read_input_tokens":58370,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":372},"output_tokens":51,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"287018b2-4458-456c-84c8-20bcb7a8b9ab","uuid":"70bf4d9c-69a8-4621-8cf9-2aa79e8fe629"}
