{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KR5QM5fJ3S5FxdsEcmREip","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All tests are passing. So the story is marked as \"passes: false\" but tests are actually green. The implementation already exists in tui.go for the phaseOpenBrowser. Let me check what acceptance criteria might be missing or not tested:\n\n1. \"After successful installation, a prompt asks the user if they want to open the store URL.\" - There's a `phaseOpenBrowser` with a prompt showing \"Open {url} in your browser?\" ✓\n2. \"Pressing `y` opens the URL in the system default browser (macOS, Linux, Windows).\" - The `y` key calls `openBrowser(url)` which handles macOS, Linux, Windows ✓\n\n\n3. \"Pressing `n` or `q` exits without opening the browser.\" - The code handles `\"n\", \"enter\", \"esc\"` but `q` is caught by the global handler at the top of `Update()` which immediately quits the app, so it would exit regardless of which phase we're in.\n\nLooking at the acceptance criteria, pressing `q` from the browser prompt would quit the app without opening the browser, and pressing `n` goes to the done screen - both satisfy the requirement.\n\n4. \"The store URL matches the configured base URL for the selected environment.\" - The view correctly uses `m.selected.Detector.BaseURL(m.installCfg.ProjectName)` to construct the URL.\n\nAll the functionality appears to be implemented, though the story is marked as failing.\n\nNow I'm checking what test coverage exists for these acceptance criteria. Looking through the tests, I see `TestUpdate_InstallDone_GoesToOpenBrowser` covers the successful install path, but there are gaps: no tests for the prompt message itself, no test for pressing `y` to open the browser, no test for pressing `n` or `q` to skip it, and no test verifying the URL matches the configured base URL. The missing piece is likely unit tests covering each acceptance criterion, so I need to examine the test file and add the missing test cases.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":224,"cache_read_input_tokens":41020,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":224},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2cb46d6e-d778-400d-a3e1-d4122c0325a3","uuid":"ff678256-862a-4598-9c30-880e63316d8c"}
