{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015uHoRizSFEm3ZwgH1hH7oQ","type":"tool_result","content":"295\t  - `internal/selfupdate/selfupdate_test.go` (new)\n296\t  - `main.go`\n297\t  - `.goreleaser.yml`\n298\t- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n299\t  - GoReleaser binary archive default name: `{project}_{version}_{os}_{arch}[.exe]` — `{{ .Version }}` strips the `v` prefix; `{{ .Os }}` matches `runtime.GOOS`; `{{ .Arch }}` matches `runtime.GOARCH`\n300\t  - Injectable `ReplaceFunc`/`ReexecFunc` are the right pattern to avoid OS-level side effects in unit tests\n301\t  - Avoid forward-referencing a `*httptest.Server`'s `.URL` inside its own handler closure — the server isn't assigned yet; use separate asset + API servers instead\n302\t  - `flag.Parse()` in `main.go` is safe for a TUI-only binary; the TUI itself reads no flags, so adding `--self-update` does not break existing usage\n303\t  - GoReleaser v2 `check` command validates ldflags syntax without a real release\n304\t---\n305\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2cb46d6e-d778-400d-a3e1-d4122c0325a3","uuid":"4dcd6b82-0dd0-4274-b0a3-292168c51f91","timestamp":"2026-04-14T19:48:37.660Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/michielgerritsen/Sites/mage-os-install/.chief/prds/main/progress.md","content":"  - `internal/selfupdate/selfupdate_test.go` (new)\n  - `main.go`\n  - `.goreleaser.yml`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - GoReleaser binary archive default name: `{project}_{version}_{os}_{arch}[.exe]` — `{{ .Version }}` strips the `v` prefix; `{{ .Os }}` matches `runtime.GOOS`; `{{ .Arch }}` matches `runtime.GOARCH`\n  - Injectable `ReplaceFunc`/`ReexecFunc` are the right pattern to avoid OS-level side effects in unit tests\n  - Avoid forward-referencing a `*httptest.Server`'s `.URL` inside its own handler closure — the server isn't assigned yet; use separate asset + API servers instead\n  - `flag.Parse()` in `main.go` is safe for a TUI-o